{
  "stem": "21786.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But there we were lucky with Eva that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we went to Theresien, and from Theresien we went to this family camp, which was a showpiece compared to anything else.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We landed there out of the trucks, and there was 5,000 people who left Theresien three months before us, a transport which left in September.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we were just gasping for-- for air, for they had, some of them, these striped uniforms, which was quite OK prepared, probably to anything.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But they acted like-- like animals, like beasts.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You know, when they came there themselves, they-- they are instructed by mostly the Polish capo, meaning from the Italian capo, means the head, C-A-P-O, that you have to be tough, you have to be brutal, you have to be really something.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then the SS men will leave you in peace and let you survive.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they tried it on us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I met there somebody who was the head of block 14, who was a lawyer whom I knew from the Zionist movement, who had seen me and he picked me to be his servant, which was tremendously lucky move at that point.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the block filled with men, guys, maybe about 500, 700 of us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The block was built, was originally, as horse stable.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "There were 40 horses, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and through it was a kind of chimney, which was [INAUDIBLE] out of bricks.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I mean a s-- a brick structure with two chimneys, which could have been fed with wood, or could have been used as heating from both sides.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Heating it wasn't, always.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Somebody was beaten-- was beaten simply that he put his head into the door of the chimney and was given, I mean, whatever he was allotted to.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
